specialize in?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1546681755992{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]We take pride in our ability to learn the fundamentals of virtually any industry or technology quickly. Some of the markets we have served include green technologies, medical devices, biotechnology, Internet/e-commerce, telecommunications, distance education/e-learning, real estate, financial services, healthcare services, manufacturing, retail, food service, consumer products, media and entertainment, aerospace, artificial intelligence, enterprise software, insurance, energy, and networking.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Can you guarantee that our plan will raise capital?" sub_title="Sub Title 2"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1540448048249{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]Of course not. Nobody can make that guarantee (and if somebody ever makes that guarantee, it’s a good idea to run away quickly). A good plan is essential, but a plan alone will not get funded. Although we will do our best to help you prepare, we have no control over how well you present yourselves to investors, or how well you answer their questions. We can coach and we can mentor, but at the end of the day, it’s your business and you must close the deal. [/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Can you help us raise money?"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1540448085794{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]We can sometimes make informal introductions to potential investors or other intermediaries. In general, only brokers licensed with the Financial Industry Regulatory Authority (FINRA) can legally arrange financing (see Beware of Finders in our Blog). Please seek legal counsel and make sure that any “finder” you talk to is properly licensed with FINRA before you hire them. Failing to do so may expose you and your company to significant liability.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Do we really need a business plan?"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1540448126120{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]If you run a business, then it’s probably safe to say yes. In fact, you may require more than one business plan: one for raising capital and one for running your business. The former is a compact, easily digested strategic document that is designed to persuade potential investors to pick up the phone and invite you to their offices for an initial meeting. The latter is a more detailed document serving as a day-to-day roadmap, detailing the tactics supporting your overall strategy. The former needs to be an attractive document that sells; the latter can be a collection of spreadsheets, lists, research summaries, and other documents stuffed in a binder that you refer to and update on a regular basis. We specialize in preparing the capital-raising business plan, but many of the by-products are suitable for use in the operating business plan.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Why should hire a consultant to our business plan?"][vc_column_text]You could easily spend 500 hours or more preparing an investor-grade business plan, financial forecast, and investor presentation, even if you have an MBA. This is time you should probably be spending building your team, product, distribution channels, and customer base. In addition to our expertise in preparing these materials, we offer independent, third-party insights into your business, and may raise questions that you might not have thought to ask.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][/vc_accordion][/vc_column][vc_column css=".vc_custom_1530614727224{padding-top: 0px !important;}" offset="vc_col-lg-6 vc_col-md-12"][vc_accordion one_active="true" title_size="20px"][vc_accordion_tab title="What makes your business plans so special?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1540448186218{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]Most importantly, they work. In a world in which fewer than 1 in 250 business plans ever raise venture capital, we are happy to report that about half of our plans have raised capital, and a good portion of the rest resulted in an acquisition or currently have commitments for investment from prior round investors. Each plan is handcrafted to reflect the client’s specific circumstances, yet share attributes that investors find appealing.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="What makes your financial projections special?" sub_title="Sub Title 2"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1540448209678{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]Balance sheets that balance. Cash flows, income statements, and balance sheets that tie together (you’d be surprised by how many consultants who don’t get the basics right). Fully assumption-driven, so that you can do what-if analyses. Depending on your needs, we can include a lot of very sophisticated features – learn more about our financial projections here.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="How long does it take?"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1540448237565{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]For a typical engagement, consisting of a business plan, financial forecast, and investor presentation, the typical time to completion is 6-8 weeks, as illustrated below. The actual time can be influenced by the quality of your existing materials, the level of your participation, the complexity of your market and business model, and our current workload.
[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Can you work any faster?"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1540448262790{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]Yes, but we may need to charge a “rush” fee. We typically work on multiple projects at any point in time, and rush projects can strain our schedules or inconvenience other clients.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="What is your refund policy?"][vc_column_text]Your initial payment is non-refundable. This is because by the time you have decided to hire us, we have already set aside time to work with you, and we may even have turned away other opportunities in order to provide you with the best possible experience. Subsequent payments are subject to a pro-rated refund if you choose to terminate the project before we have fully earned the subsequent payment. For example, suppose fees for your project are broken into three payments, each covering 20 hours of services. [/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][/vc_accordion][/vc_column][/vc_row]

item.content:encoded: [vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="Privacy Policy" font_container="tag:h3|font_size:30px|text_align:left|color:%23333333|line_height:43px" google_fonts="font_family:Montserrat%3Aregular%2C700|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal" css=".vc_custom_1536150978588{padding-bottom: 15px !important;}"][vc_custom_heading text="Summary:" font_container="tag:h3|font_size:20px|text_align:left|color:%23333333|line_height:43px" use_theme_fonts="yes"][vc_column_text]business takes technology to businesses, consumers and, society in a way that makes amazing experiences possible but doesn’t come at the expense of your privacy. We believe in change and performance that supports your privacy rights and in technology designed with those rights in mind. In particular, this Separation Notice explains how our goods, services and, technologies use your personal information. It applies to our use of personal information across our websites, products, online services, software, apps, tools, and other services and functionality we provide, both online and offline (collectively referred to as “Havnor® Services”), unless a separate, or supplementary, privacy notice is offered. See “Additional Privacy Notices and Supplements” for additional information posted for specific Havnor® Services. at https://www.havnor.com/en-us/locations/.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row overlay_dotted="" css=".vc_custom_1536151740300{border-top-width: 1px !important;border-right-width: 1px !important;border-bottom-width: 1px !important;border-left-width: 1px !important;padding-right: 30px !important;padding-left: 30px !important;background-color: #ffffff !important;border-left-color: #e5e5e5 !important;border-left-style: solid !important;border-right-color: #e5e5e5 !important;border-right-style: solid !important;border-top-color: #e5e5e5 !important;border-top-style: solid !important;border-bottom-color: #e5e5e5 !important;border-bottom-style: solid !important;}"][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="1. Personal Data Privacy - General" font_container="tag:h4|font_size:20px|text_align:left|color:%23333333|line_height:27px" use_theme_fonts="yes"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1539089630567{margin-bottom: 20px !important;}"]1.1 Havnor collects information as part of its business operations, to provide services, to respond to requests and offer customer support, to fulfill legal and contractual responsibilities and to develop its innovative products. You provide some of this data directly, such as when you order an Havnor product, contact customer support, or register for an Havnor event or publication. We also collect information into your interaction with Havnor® Services and our website, for example, using embedded product technologies and cookies. We also obtain data from third parties.[/vc_column_text][vc_separator color="custom" accent_color="#dcdcdc"][vc_custom_heading text="2. Information You Provide to Havnor Voluntarily" font_container="tag:h4|font_size:20px|text_align:left|color:%23333333|line_height:27px" use_theme_fonts="yes"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1539089681678{margin-bottom: 20px !important;}"]1.1 When you subscribe to a newsletter, create an account, make a purchase or request information from Havnor, we will ask for things like contact, billing, shipping and communication information, payment card or financial account data, and account ID or credentials in order to fulfill your request. If you visit one of our stores or locations, attend a trade show or event, or otherwise contact us, you may also voluntarily provide similar information. Interactive stories in some Havnor Services may allow you to invite friends, follow others, comment on or make unique posts, or share photos, video or other personal content. item.title: Eyeline Creatives
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Eyeline Creatives

There is something special when creative people get together. Being inexhaustible, life and nature are a constant stimulus for a creative mind. It is the supreme art of the teacher to awaken joy in creative expression and knowledge.

Unique Approach

To create something exceptional, your mindset must be relentlessly focused on the smallest detail. The creation of something new is not accomplished by the intellect but by the play instinct acting from inner necessity. The creative mind plays with the objects it loves. Being inexhaustible, life and nature are a constant stimulus for a creative mind.

Create The Best

It is the supreme art of the teacher to awaken joy in creative expression and knowledge. The uncreative mind can spot wrong answers, but it takes a very creative mind to spot wrong questions.

%22partners_text%22%3A%22Havnor%20provides%20a%20full%20suite%20of%20services%20to%20enable%20customers%20to%20maximize%20their%20investment%20in%20Ipsum%20and%20Salesforce%20by%20leveraging%20our%20certified%20experts%20for%20Implementation%20%26%20Consulting%2C%20Optimization%20Services%2C%20Havnor%20%26%20Salesforce%20Administration%2C%20and%20Custom%20App%20Development.%22%7D%2C%7B%22partners_title%22%3A%22About%20Infinity%22%2C%22partners_text%22%3A%22Havnor%20believes%20that%20nonprofit%20organizations%20should%20have%20the%20same%20access%20to%20results%20as%20for-profit%20businesses.%20In%202000%2C%20this%20belief%20launched%20The%20infinity%20Group%2C%20The%20first%20firm%20to%20deliver%20high-level%20strategy%20consulting%20services%20to%20the%20nonprofit%20sector.%22%7D%2C%7B%22partners_title%22%3A%22About%20Cropit%20Partner%22%2C%22partners_text%22%3A%22Crop%20it%20is%20a%20global%20nonprofit%20that%20seeks%20to%20catalyze%20long-term%20economic%20growth%20by%20supporting%20high-impact%20entrepreneurs%20around%20the%20world.%20Havnor%20is%20a%20proud%20supporter%2C%20have%20partnered%20to%20develop%20and%20implement%20both%20crop%20it's%20global%20and%20country-level%20strategies.%22%7D%2C%7B%22partners_title%22%3A%22About%20Dynamic%22%2C%22partners_text%22%3A%22Dynamics%20mission%20is%20to%20change%20the%20way%20the%20world%20tackles%20poverty%20by%20investing%20in%20companies%2C%20leaders%2C%20and%20ideas.%20So%20far%2C%20it%20has%20invested%20more%20than%20%2480%20million%20around%20the%20world.%22%7D%2C%7B%22partners_title%22%3A%22About%20Hitch%22%2C%22partners_text%22%3A%22The%20hitch%20is%20a%20cloud-computing%20platform%20known%20for%20intelligent%20workflows%20and%20automation%20that%20Booz%20Allen%20uses%20to%20enable%20Enterprise%20Transformation%20for%20client%20organizations.%20With%20ServiceNow%2C%20organizations%20no%20longer%20need%20to%20spend%20time%20defining%20ITIL-compliant%20processes.%22%7D%2C%7B%22partners_title%22%3A%22About%20Esquare%22%2C%22partners_text%22%3A%22The%20Esquire%20leads%20engagement%20with%20G20%20governments%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20international%20business%20community.%20Havnor%20is%20a%20Knowledge%20Partner%20for%20B20%20Argentina%202018%2C%20leading%20the%20Sustainable%20Food%20System%20task%20force.%22%7D%2C%7B%22partners_title%22%3A%22About%20Groshvin%22%2C%22partners_text%22%3A%22Groshvin%20is%20a%20unique%20global%20platform%20that%20invests%20in%20empowering%20girls%20and%20women%20around%20the%20world.%20Designed%20according%20to%20the%20G20%20architecture%2C%20the%20Groshvin%20Summit%20brings%20together%20one%20delegate%20from%20each%20G20%20country%2C%22%7D%5D" There is something special when creative people get together. Being inexhaustible, life and nature are a constant stimulus for a creative mind.

Unique Approach

To create something exceptional, your mindset must be relentlessly focused on the smallest detail. Being inexhaustible, life and nature are a constant stimulus for a creative mind.

Create The Best

It is the supreme art of the teacher to awaken joy in creative expression and knowledge. The uncreative mind can spot wrong answers, but it takes a very creative mind to spot wrong questions.

item.title: Cheaper and Easier
item.content:encoded:
This classic book, now in its third edition, supplies a step-by-step guide to the whole territory: 'how to assemble a budget', 'how to read variances on a report', 'how to construct a proposal to invest in new equipment'.
By examining the actual things that managers have to do, each chapter explores the range of principles that can be applied, illustrates practical techniques and provides general guidance.
item.excerpt:encoded: The world of finance can be a minefield for the unwary. Without training, very few managers are prepared for the challenges of dealing with management reports, budgets and capital proposals, and find themselves embarrassed by their lack of understanding.

item.title: Great Content
item.content:encoded: The book is packed with colorful illustrations and covers important aspects of financial dealings for an individual. This book will enable the readers understand how to enhance financial security and avoid fraud and losses from corrupt agents and dubious schemes. 108 Mantras for Financial Success is a must-have for investors, housewives and management students.
item.excerpt:encoded: This book has been conceived and conceptualized under IIFL’s Financial Literacy Agenda for Mass Empowerment initiative towards increasing financial literacy among people.

item.title: Business Success
item.content:encoded: It is now well established fact that the success of any business concern depends inter-alia upon the efficiency with which funds are being managed. As such, management students must have an opportunity to gain effective knowledge of various aspects of finance i.e., procurement and utilisation of funds in an optimal way. That is why there is a separate paper/subject of `Financial Management' almost in every curriculum of BBA/MBA programmes run by University Departments or B Schools.
item.excerpt:encoded: Preface Management education in our country has recently experienced a sea-change in its curriculum, wherein electives in finance and marketing have been enlarged. In fact, finance has assumed greater significance for all those pursuing a management course or its allied.
